Hi Matt: Here is the HTML: &lt;div class="hs-search-results"&gt;
  &lt;template class="hs-search-results__template"&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;
      &lt;a href="#" class="hs-search-results__title"&gt;Content Title&lt;/a&gt;
      &lt;p class="hs-search-results__description"&gt;Description&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;/template&gt;
  &lt;ul id="hsresults" class="hs-search-results__listing"&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;
  &lt;div class="hs-search-results__pagination" data-search-path="{{ site_settings.content_search_results_page_path }}"&gt;
    &lt;a href="" class="hs-search-results__prev-page"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;a href="" class="hs-search-results__next-page"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

The search bar should look like this then:{# Need help setting up site search?
   Start here: <https://knowledge.HubSpot.com/articles/kcs_article/cos-general/how-do-i-set-up-a-results-page-for-my-search-field-in-HubSpot> #}

&lt;div class="hs-search-field"&gt;
    &lt;div class="hs-search-field__bar"&gt;
      &lt;h3&gt;{{ module.sst_heading }}&lt;/h3&gt;
      &lt;form action="/{{ site_settings.content_search_results_page_path }}"&gt;
        &lt;label&gt;{{ module.sstclabel_text }}&lt;/label&gt;
        &lt;input type="text" class="hs-search-field__input" name="term" autocomplete="off" placeholder="{{ module.placeholder }}"&gt;
        &lt;input type="hidden" name="domain" value="<http://creditcardprocessing.apspayments.com|creditcardprocessing.apspayments.com>"&gt;
        &lt;input type="hidden" name="domain" value="<http://apspayments.com|apspayments.com>"&gt;
        {#
        DEVELOPERS: You can set additional search parameters by adding hidden
        inputs like the example below. Both the typeahead and search results
        modules will accept these, except 'limit' which only works for results.

       	&lt;input type="hidden" name="limit" value="5"&gt;
        #}
      &lt;/form&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;ul class="hs-search-field__suggestions"&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

